WEBVTT

00:00.195 --> 00:02.281
ALEX: <i>All my life,
my second cousin Eddie</i>

00:02.352 --> 00:03.765
<i>has believed he knows
what's best for me.</i>

00:03.836 --> 00:05.828
I'll have a passion fruit
iced tea, please.

00:05.883 --> 00:07.849
Wrong! He'll have a medium chai.

00:07.918 --> 00:09.418
- Extra dirty.
- Oh, no, thanks.

00:09.486 --> 00:11.382
I'm not a chai guy or a dirty guy.

00:11.437 --> 00:12.870
Trust me. That's the move here.

00:12.939 --> 00:15.006
I'm gonna turn you into a dirty guy.

00:15.074 --> 00:17.208
Oh, that's not what it
sounds like. We're cousins.

00:17.276 --> 00:19.310
I've had to tell this guy
what he likes his whole life.

00:19.379 --> 00:20.778
He was too scared...

00:20.847 --> 00:22.446
<i>Yep. It's always Eddie knows best.</i>

00:22.515 --> 00:23.981
<i>And occasionally, he does.</i>

00:24.050 --> 00:26.317
But other times, I mean,
take this Incubator,

00:26.386 --> 00:28.219
for example, right? Eddie found it

00:28.321 --> 00:31.589
and talked me into signing
this ridiculously long lease.

00:31.624 --> 00:34.091
It's not exactly perfect for
what we do here because...

00:34.160 --> 00:36.193
[Dog barks]

00:36.295 --> 00:37.628
Because of that.

00:37.697 --> 00:39.664
Why are there dogs in the Incubator?

00:39.732 --> 00:41.565
Oh, they're with that new
start-up "Ruff Timez".

00:41.634 --> 00:43.267
It's an app that pairs depressed people

00:43.336 --> 00:44.669
with dogs who need companions.

00:44.737 --> 00:46.904
Oh, I assumed that was
a newspaper for dogs

00:46.973 --> 00:48.472
and all those guys were the editors.

00:48.541 --> 00:51.275
The singing landlord doesn't help.

00:51.344 --> 00:52.410
[Singing opera]

00:52.512 --> 00:54.011
Good morning, Marion.

00:54.113 --> 00:56.213
Well, good morning, Alex.
What's the good word?

00:56.282 --> 00:57.915
Well, you know, I'm trying
to record my podcast.

00:57.984 --> 00:59.279
[Chuckles] Good luck.

00:59.349 --> 01:00.934
- It's loud in here, huh?
- Yeah.

01:00.987 --> 01:04.488
[Singing continues]

01:04.557 --> 01:05.790
I think we're gonna need...

01:05.858 --> 01:07.925
[Blow dryer whirrs]

01:07.960 --> 01:11.062
- ...to do some offsite recording!
- On it!

01:11.130 --> 01:13.064
Al, get ready.

01:13.166 --> 01:17.201
You are about to be famous.

01:19.639 --> 01:20.871
What the hell is that?

01:20.940 --> 01:23.240
Strategically placed bus-bench ads.

01:23.309 --> 01:24.909
It's called "creating buzz".

01:24.977 --> 01:27.244
It looks like he's doing
a podcast about construction.

01:27.313 --> 01:29.213
O-Or I'm a Village Person
who's been shunned

01:29.315 --> 01:30.347
by the other Village People.

01:30.450 --> 01:32.283
Either way, gets people talking.

01:32.385 --> 01:33.517
Yeah, it gets them talking about a guy

01:33.586 --> 01:35.453
who's in love with his extension cord.

01:35.521 --> 01:36.687
Who told you to do bus ads?

01:36.756 --> 01:39.523
Nobody needed to tell me.
I knew it intuitively.

01:39.592 --> 01:41.892
This is a really bad idea
on so many levels, okay?

01:41.961 --> 01:44.428
We can't afford this,
we don't even have an air-date,

01:44.464 --> 01:45.996
it's a horrible picture of me,

01:46.065 --> 01:47.665
and even if you could tell who it is,

01:47.767 --> 01:49.467
nobody knows who I am.

01:49.569 --> 01:51.135
Okay, now do the pros.

01:52.705 --> 01:56.945
<font color="#0080ff">Synced & corrected by</font> kinglouisxx
<font color="#0080ff">www.</font>addic7ed<font color="#0080ff">.com</font>

01:57.944 --> 01:59.243
[Cellphone chimes]

01:59.345 --> 02:02.413
Ugh. People keep sending me
pictures of these bus-bench ads.

02:02.515 --> 02:04.415
Some of them don't even have penises

02:04.517 --> 02:06.417
drawn on them, like this one.

02:06.519 --> 02:07.585
Oh, no.

02:07.687 --> 02:09.687
- There it is.
- It's on my ear.

02:09.788 --> 02:10.788
- Looks mad.
- Mm.

02:10.857 --> 02:12.656
Can you believe he did this?

02:12.725 --> 02:14.658
I mean, I'm the boss...
this is a big deal.

02:14.761 --> 02:16.660
If I wanted my face plastered
all over the place,

02:16.763 --> 02:18.095
it should be my decision.

02:18.197 --> 02:20.231
At least I would have chosen
a more flattering picture.

02:20.299 --> 02:23.067
All these penises are
highlighting my weak chin.

02:23.169 --> 02:24.568
Well, if you want things
to be different,

02:24.670 --> 02:25.903
you just got to talk to him.

02:26.005 --> 02:27.371
Oh, I wish there was another option.

02:27.473 --> 02:29.874
- I'm not great at confronting Eddie.
- Hmm.

02:29.976 --> 02:32.143
Well, I guess you could
just not talk to him

02:32.245 --> 02:34.779
and hope that someday
the dynamic magically changes.

02:34.881 --> 02:37.348
I like that one because
it has no confrontation,

02:37.450 --> 02:38.849
and there's a magic element.

02:40.186 --> 02:41.552
Fine, I'll talk to him.

02:41.654 --> 02:44.155
Hey, Dad! Look what I found
in the basement!

02:44.257 --> 02:45.923
Look at that!

02:46.025 --> 02:49.093
My old guitar... the "Beige Dragon".

02:49.195 --> 02:50.361
I'm gonna learn how to play it.

02:50.463 --> 02:53.197
But I got to warn you, learning
to play is pretty hard.

02:53.299 --> 02:55.933
I spent many a year grinding on that ax,

02:56.035 --> 02:58.469
only to be left with some
tear-stained frets

02:58.571 --> 03:01.105
and the first two chords
of "Eye of the Tiger".

03:01.207 --> 03:04.408
All I heard was "Ben, I'm old".

03:04.510 --> 03:07.478
- I am, Ben. I am.
- SORAYA: Hey, Dad.

03:07.580 --> 03:09.213
Ms. Conway said
our field trip chaperones

03:09.315 --> 03:11.282
have to be there
Wednesday morning at 8:00.

03:11.384 --> 03:12.750
Oh, chaperoning.

03:12.852 --> 03:14.585
I forgot about that field trip, babe.

03:14.654 --> 03:15.886
But it's the Butterfly Pavilion.

03:15.988 --> 03:17.688
You love the Butterfly Pavilion.

03:17.790 --> 03:19.456
More than you could ever know...

03:19.559 --> 03:22.359
with the beautiful blue morphos
and the monarchs

03:22.461 --> 03:24.028
and that hummingbird who's
probably not even

03:24.096 --> 03:25.930
supposed to be there.
I wonder what his story is.

03:26.032 --> 03:28.132
But I can't babe, I'm so busy with work.

03:28.201 --> 03:30.467
Well, I guess they'll have
to find another parent.

03:30.536 --> 03:32.069
What, excuse me?

03:32.171 --> 03:33.904
Is there anything you'd like to ask me?

03:34.006 --> 03:36.473
Yeah. What can't Dad
come to my field trip?

03:36.576 --> 03:37.808
I'm a parent, too, you know.

03:37.910 --> 03:39.410
Yeah, but you never do field trips.

03:39.512 --> 03:40.644
You're always too busy working.

03:40.746 --> 03:41.946
Not "never".

03:42.048 --> 03:43.480
I took you to the aquarium.

03:43.583 --> 03:45.916
That was a lobster tank
at a seafood restaurant.

03:46.018 --> 03:47.618
[Sighs]

03:47.720 --> 03:50.020
Oh, my God, I'm a monster!

03:50.122 --> 03:53.924
No, but you did manage to eat
the one lobster she named.

03:54.026 --> 03:55.025
Poor Clawsy.

03:55.127 --> 03:56.493
No. No, I'm serious.

03:56.596 --> 03:58.028
This is a wake-up call for me.

03:58.130 --> 03:59.430
I always thought we were a team

03:59.532 --> 04:01.265
and I got credit for you doing stuff,

04:01.367 --> 04:03.000
but I guess she saw right through that.

04:03.102 --> 04:04.335
I don't want my daughter to think

04:04.437 --> 04:06.270
I'm not involved in her life.

04:06.372 --> 04:07.872
You know what, I'm gonna
call Ms. Hopkins

04:07.974 --> 04:09.206
and tell her I want to chaperone.

04:09.308 --> 04:10.641
Great, but call Ms. Conway,

04:10.743 --> 04:12.343
'cause Hopkins was last year.

04:13.112 --> 04:14.144
Shut up.

04:14.247 --> 04:15.779
Sweetie!

04:15.882 --> 04:17.147
Guess what.

04:17.250 --> 04:18.716
I'm going on your butterfly field trip.

04:18.784 --> 04:19.850
- Really?!
- Yes.

04:19.952 --> 04:21.151
- Thanks, Mommy.
- You got it, babe.

04:21.254 --> 04:22.620
I recommend the audio tour...

04:22.722 --> 04:24.521
it's narrated by Mickey Rourke.

04:24.624 --> 04:25.890
He's a fellow Butterfly-Boy.

04:27.260 --> 04:29.693
Well, I found a few places
we could do a recording.

04:29.795 --> 04:31.028
The best rate is $100 an hour,

04:31.130 --> 04:32.863
but with that one you have
to sign a rabies waiver...

04:32.965 --> 04:34.298
apparently, they're
having a raccoon issue.

04:34.400 --> 04:35.666
EDDIE: Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa.

04:35.768 --> 04:37.835
Why are we renting space?

04:37.937 --> 04:39.069
We're already renting this space.

04:39.171 --> 04:40.971
I could just build us
a booth right here.

04:41.073 --> 04:42.740
You know what, Ed,
I appreciate the enthusiasm,

04:42.842 --> 04:44.642
but I don't think that's the way to go.

04:44.744 --> 04:46.744
For starters, there's
no room for a booth here,

04:46.812 --> 04:48.245
and we'd have to get,
like, a million people

04:48.347 --> 04:49.313
to sign off on it.

04:49.415 --> 04:50.514
I'm just not sure it's worth the hassle.

04:50.616 --> 04:52.316
I know you're not sure.
You're never sure.

04:52.418 --> 04:53.550
That's why you got me.

04:53.653 --> 04:54.852
You weren't sure it was a good idea

04:54.954 --> 04:56.053
to shave your head that summer,

04:56.122 --> 04:57.521
so I did it while you were asleep.

04:57.623 --> 04:59.857
And if I'm not mistaken,
that was the same summer

04:59.959 --> 05:01.058
you almost lost your virginity.

05:01.160 --> 05:02.159
We're not building a booth.

05:02.261 --> 05:03.427
We're going with Deirdre's thing.

05:03.529 --> 05:04.728
Okay, but we should move quickly.

05:04.797 --> 05:07.364
If I've already had rabies,
can I get it again?

05:07.466 --> 05:09.800
Oh, when we were kids,
Eddie made me pet a possum.

05:09.902 --> 05:12.303
He was so soft...

05:12.405 --> 05:14.338
- till he bit me.
- Aww.

05:14.440 --> 05:16.540
Good times.

05:16.642 --> 05:19.710
[Guitar plays blues riff]

05:25.351 --> 05:27.684
Oh, my God. That was amazing!

05:27.762 --> 05:29.420
Yesterday, you hadn't
even touched a guitar.

05:29.488 --> 05:31.221
- How the hell did you learn to...
- YouTube.

05:31.257 --> 05:33.123
I watched a couple of
instructional videos...

05:33.159 --> 05:35.793
pretty simple. I can also
make slime blindfolded

05:35.861 --> 05:37.661
- and clean a musket.
- Wow!

05:37.730 --> 05:39.530
See, if I had had the Internet
when I was learning,

05:39.598 --> 05:40.798
it would have been
a whole different story.

05:40.866 --> 05:43.167
That doesn't feel true, does it, Dad?

05:43.269 --> 05:44.501
No.

05:44.603 --> 05:45.869
No, it doesn't.

05:45.938 --> 05:47.571
So, Dad, I was thinking

05:47.640 --> 05:49.940
you're gonna need a music guy
to score your podcast,

05:50.009 --> 05:52.009
I would like to throw
my hat into the ring.

05:52.111 --> 05:54.912
Oh, Ben, composing for a podcast

05:54.981 --> 05:57.214
- is actually quite complicated.
- Is it?

05:57.316 --> 05:59.216
Don't you just need someone
to underscore

05:59.285 --> 06:01.051
the emotion of whatever's happening?

06:01.120 --> 06:04.321
- Well, kind of, but...
- Don't you mean "exactly"?

06:04.390 --> 06:06.290
Well, i-it's just not really

06:06.392 --> 06:09.259
an appropriate job for a 12-year-old.

06:09.328 --> 06:13.263
[Somber tune plays]

06:13.366 --> 06:14.898
I see what you're doing.

06:15.001 --> 06:17.101
Hey, Al, so on these field trips,

06:17.136 --> 06:19.403
do the buses have outlets
so I can charge my laptop?

06:19.505 --> 06:21.438
[Laughs] Oh, wife.

06:21.507 --> 06:24.908
Oh, sweet, adorable, naive wife.

06:25.011 --> 06:26.944
You're not gonna get any work done.

06:27.013 --> 06:30.080
They're gonna be coming at you
from all sides, okay?

06:30.149 --> 06:32.182
Zoe S. gets carsick,

06:32.284 --> 06:34.451
so you're gonna have to
remind her not to read.

06:34.520 --> 06:36.620
Zoe F. is allergic to everything

06:36.689 --> 06:39.390
and yet is the most adventurous
eater in the whole grade.

06:39.492 --> 06:42.793
- Noah B. needs his five minutes.
- Five minutes?

06:42.862 --> 06:44.361
He's a budding stand-up comedian.

06:44.463 --> 06:45.729
Okay, listen.

06:45.765 --> 06:47.164
I'm gonna be fine.

06:47.233 --> 06:49.233
- I got this.
- I want to be supportive.

06:49.335 --> 06:50.734
I really do, but I'm not gonna lie...

06:50.803 --> 06:52.302
I'm kind of scared for you.

06:52.371 --> 06:55.672
[Aggressive tune plays]

06:55.775 --> 06:57.107
This is not a job interview.

06:57.209 --> 06:58.409
Get out of here. Skedaddle.

06:59.545 --> 07:01.445
Such a show-off. He's a show-off.

07:04.517 --> 07:05.749
You're here early.

07:05.851 --> 07:08.352
Yeah, well, I got to show you something.

07:08.421 --> 07:10.988
Got a big surprise for you.

07:11.090 --> 07:12.523
Ha ha! See?

07:12.591 --> 07:13.690
I knew you'd love it.

07:13.793 --> 07:15.125
Brand-new recording booth.

07:15.194 --> 07:16.794
I told you not to do this.

07:16.862 --> 07:18.462
But this solves all our problems.

07:18.564 --> 07:20.097
- I want you to take it down.
- What?!

07:20.199 --> 07:22.332
- Oh, my God!
- ALEX: I know, right?

07:22.401 --> 07:23.467
This booth is incredible.

07:23.569 --> 07:26.003
Alex, this might be your best idea yet.

07:26.105 --> 07:27.171
Today is the day that Alex Schuman

07:27.273 --> 07:28.539
became President of this company.

07:28.607 --> 07:30.340
Do you hear that?
Deirdre loves the booth.

07:30.376 --> 07:31.742
It's not that great. Come on.

07:31.811 --> 07:32.876
Oh, you are being too modest.

07:32.945 --> 07:34.445
A two-person recording booth,
right here?

07:34.547 --> 07:36.680
- I mean, it's genius.
- It only cost 1,100 bucks.

07:36.749 --> 07:38.782
- What?! That's...
- An incredible price.

07:38.851 --> 07:40.651
Okay, stop saying nice things
about the booth.

07:40.686 --> 07:41.919
Eddie did it without permission.

07:42.021 --> 07:43.253
Because there's no downside.

07:43.355 --> 07:45.189
- What the hell is this?
- He did it.

07:45.291 --> 07:46.790
There was no permission
and it was all his fault.

07:46.892 --> 07:47.958
And I'm mad, too.

07:48.060 --> 07:49.693
Okay, this is a communal space.

07:49.795 --> 07:50.961
If you want to use it,
I'm gonna have to start

07:51.063 --> 07:53.430
- charging you... a lot.
- Downside!

07:53.499 --> 07:54.832
Okay, Marion, let's talk about this.

07:54.900 --> 07:56.433
Sure. And what we can talk about

07:56.502 --> 07:59.203
is me charging you an extra...

07:59.305 --> 08:00.504
400 bucks a month?

08:00.606 --> 08:02.206
- Yeah, good talk.
- That's it. Take it down.

08:02.308 --> 08:04.775
Alex, can I have a word?

08:04.844 --> 08:06.343
Okay, I know you're mad at Eddie,

08:06.479 --> 08:07.678
but I would just like to point out

08:07.746 --> 08:08.979
that I have done a lot of research

08:09.081 --> 08:10.514
on offsite recording spaces.

08:10.616 --> 08:11.882
And even with the rent increase,

08:11.984 --> 08:13.350
this would still be a way better deal

08:13.452 --> 08:14.451
than anything else out there.

08:14.553 --> 08:15.819
Deirdre, I can't cave on this.

08:15.888 --> 08:17.688
I-It's the principle of the thing.

08:17.756 --> 08:19.256
You are letting your pride
get in the way.

08:19.358 --> 08:20.858
It's amazing!

08:20.960 --> 08:23.694
Okay, fine, but I'm still mad.

08:23.796 --> 08:27.030
Eddie, Marion, we'll pay for it.

08:27.099 --> 08:30.267
Well, that was easy.
Should've asked for $700.

08:30.369 --> 08:32.369
Always ask for $700, you know that.

08:32.471 --> 08:34.171
Eddie, from here on out,

08:34.240 --> 08:36.707
do not make any decisions
without running it by me first.

08:36.808 --> 08:39.275
- Are we clear?
- Okay, cuz, whatever you say.

08:39.378 --> 08:41.145
He's very cute
when he's upset, isn't he?

08:41.246 --> 08:43.179
My ma used to call him
the "Little Volcano".

08:43.249 --> 08:45.716
And stop telling stories
about when I was little!

08:45.751 --> 08:48.633
And that right there is what
she'd call a major eruption.

08:51.110 --> 08:53.414
[Kids shouting]

08:53.469 --> 08:54.912
How many bodies?

08:54.981 --> 08:56.447
Just eyeball it, Lydia.

08:56.515 --> 08:58.604
Well, was there DNA on the scene?

08:58.675 --> 09:00.375
Dad never works on the bus.

09:00.443 --> 09:02.744
Well, no one knows
if Dad's job is real, sweetie.

09:02.812 --> 09:05.146
Oh, Zoe F.! I don't know where
you got those Nutter-Butters,

09:05.248 --> 09:07.215
but maybe wait until
we're near an epi-pen

09:07.317 --> 09:08.716
before you eat them.

09:08.785 --> 09:10.318
No, I haven't seen the "Saw" films.

09:10.387 --> 09:12.287
Are there other movies
you can compare it to?

09:12.322 --> 09:14.822
Hi, Zoe S.

09:14.891 --> 09:16.958
Why you holding a book?

09:17.060 --> 09:19.093
Zoe S.? No, no, no, no.

09:19.162 --> 09:20.128
CHILD: Ohh!

09:20.230 --> 09:21.930
Ooh, clean up on aisle 10.

09:22.032 --> 09:23.665
WOMAN: Turn around, Noah B.

09:23.733 --> 09:25.600
I'm gonna have to call you back.

09:25.669 --> 09:27.869
<i>All day long, it was like that
booth was staring at me,</i>

09:27.938 --> 09:29.570
<i>saying, "So I guess
you're gonna keep letting Eddie</i>

09:29.673 --> 09:31.105
<i>walk all over you, huh?"</i>

09:31.141 --> 09:33.007
<i>Well, watch this, you stupid booth.</i>

09:33.076 --> 09:35.410
Al! Just got off the phone
with a lady who'll give us

09:35.512 --> 09:37.645
faster Internet for the same price.

09:37.714 --> 09:39.781
Thank you for bringing that
to my attention, Ed.

09:39.816 --> 09:41.749
- I'll consider it.
- You need to consider

09:41.818 --> 09:42.984
whether you want faster Internet?

09:43.086 --> 09:44.719
I don't like it when it goes too fast.

09:44.788 --> 09:45.853
But when you upload your podcasts,

09:45.956 --> 09:47.422
it takes a really long time.

09:47.457 --> 09:49.324
Yes, which builds up anticipation.

09:49.392 --> 09:50.825
Thank you.

09:50.927 --> 09:52.927
Oh, no, quickly, shut the door.

09:52.996 --> 09:55.029
A monarch is headed for an escape.

09:57.167 --> 09:58.866
Saved ya, buddy!

09:58.935 --> 10:00.468
Remember, kids,

10:00.537 --> 10:03.338
each one of these butterflies
is incredibly precious.

10:03.406 --> 10:05.039
So, be careful of your surroundings

10:05.141 --> 10:06.441
while you're in the pavilion.

10:06.509 --> 10:09.143
And be on the lookout
for the blue morpho...

10:09.245 --> 10:11.537
- the rarest butterfly here.
- [Kids gasping]

10:11.591 --> 10:15.116
We only have one, and it's
almost impossible to find him.

10:15.218 --> 10:16.884
Mom!

10:16.987 --> 10:18.152
Sorry, sweetie.

10:18.254 --> 10:20.722
Now, if everyone can get super quiet,

10:20.790 --> 10:23.725
you can almost hear
the fluttering of their wings.

10:24.828 --> 10:26.461
[Cellphone rings]

10:26.529 --> 10:28.529
- So sorry...
- [Ringing continues]

10:28.631 --> 10:30.498
Ah, yeah, I have to, um...

10:30.600 --> 10:32.400
you know what, I do think
I hear some fluttering

10:32.502 --> 10:33.534
over in that direction.

10:33.636 --> 10:34.969
What's up?

10:35.005 --> 10:36.604
WOMAN: Okay, kids, if you could
look over here...

10:36.706 --> 10:38.172
Why? I didn't say that.

10:38.241 --> 10:39.607
- I never said that.
- [Crunching]

10:39.709 --> 10:41.542
- [Children gasp]
- What?

10:43.646 --> 10:46.014
Soraya's mom killed the blue morpho!

10:46.082 --> 10:47.849
SORAYA: Mom!

10:48.985 --> 10:50.351
Found it.

10:53.656 --> 10:55.523
<i>Part of me knew I was
acting like a child,</i>

10:55.592 --> 10:56.758
<i>but in my head, it was Eddie's fault</i>

10:56.860 --> 10:58.893
<i>for treating me like one.</i>

10:58.962 --> 11:00.962
- Ugh.
- <i>And now I couldn't stop.</i>

11:01.031 --> 11:02.530
Oh, God. What's that smell?

11:02.565 --> 11:04.432
Some of this food has been
sitting here forever.

11:04.501 --> 11:06.768
- I'm getting rid of it.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, Eddie.

11:06.836 --> 11:08.703
I should probably be
the one to decide that.

11:08.772 --> 11:10.705
Decide whether to throw out rotten food?

11:10.740 --> 11:13.007
Absolutely. Please put
that guy back in there.

11:13.076 --> 11:14.275
- Thank you.
- Come on, Al.

11:14.344 --> 11:15.576
- This is ridiculous.
- Is it?

11:15.678 --> 11:16.878
What if somebody at our company

11:16.980 --> 11:18.246
was planning on eating that sandwich?

11:18.348 --> 11:19.447
Like who?

11:20.850 --> 11:22.216
Me.

11:22.285 --> 11:24.719
I've had my eye on that guy
for a few weeks now.

11:24.821 --> 11:27.622
It's rotten. It smells like an old shoe.

11:27.690 --> 11:30.458
Well, Eddie, some things
are better aged...

11:30.527 --> 11:33.861
wine, cheese, Clooney.

11:33.930 --> 11:35.897
Mmm, old Clooney.

11:35.999 --> 11:39.100
Well, it's almost lunchtime.

11:39.169 --> 11:40.835
Why don't you eat it now?

11:45.608 --> 11:47.475
I will.

11:47.577 --> 11:49.077
Thank you for bringing it to me.

11:49.145 --> 11:50.778
Enjoy.

11:50.847 --> 11:52.680
I plan to.

11:54.250 --> 11:56.250
Alex...

11:56.352 --> 11:58.319
Hoo!

11:58.421 --> 12:05.493
♪

12:05.595 --> 12:06.561
[Whimpers]

12:06.629 --> 12:08.062
Glad I didn't throw it out.

12:08.164 --> 12:10.031
Me, too.

12:10.133 --> 12:11.365
All right, you know what, that's it.

12:11.468 --> 12:13.000
- Can I speak to you in private?
- Mm-hmm.

12:13.069 --> 12:14.469
I'm gonna save this for later.

12:14.571 --> 12:16.704
Thank you.

12:16.806 --> 12:19.407
Okay, I think I've figured out
what's going on here.

12:19.476 --> 12:21.976
You're angry you didn't have
the idea for this booth.

12:22.078 --> 12:24.245
So how about we tell everyone
it was your idea?

12:24.347 --> 12:25.580
- Good?
- No, not good.

12:25.648 --> 12:26.948
You're missing the point entirely.

12:27.050 --> 12:29.317
This booth is a monument to the fact

12:29.385 --> 12:31.119
that you think you always
know what's best for me.

12:31.221 --> 12:33.054
- Well, oftentimes I do.
- No!

12:33.123 --> 12:34.322
No, you don't, okay?

12:34.390 --> 12:37.425
I am not little baby cousin Alex anymore

12:37.527 --> 12:39.227
who you can just push around.

12:39.295 --> 12:40.862
I am the boss of this company,

12:40.930 --> 12:42.530
and you need to start
understanding that.

12:42.632 --> 12:44.665
Ooh, boy, eruption coming.

12:44.734 --> 12:46.767
See! Don't do that!
I hate it when you do that!

12:46.870 --> 12:47.802
- Stop it.
- Or what?

12:47.871 --> 12:49.337
You don't even want to know what.

12:49.405 --> 12:50.538
Will it be lava-related?

12:50.607 --> 12:52.006
It might be something like this.

12:52.108 --> 12:53.674
Oh! Did you just push me?

12:53.776 --> 12:56.144
Yeah, yeah. And I might again.

12:56.246 --> 12:58.146
Oh!

12:58.281 --> 12:59.180
[Grunting]

12:59.282 --> 13:01.048
Tried of you al... You are such a...

13:01.151 --> 13:02.717
This is what you used
to do when we were kids.

13:02.819 --> 13:04.118
And I hated it!

13:05.188 --> 13:07.054
Oh, I swear to God...

13:07.157 --> 13:08.990
- Here it comes.
- Aah!

13:10.326 --> 13:11.492
Oh!

13:11.594 --> 13:13.828
[People gasp]

13:13.930 --> 13:15.429
God!

13:15.532 --> 13:17.999
I never should have hired you
in the first place!

13:22.071 --> 13:24.772
You seem upset. Meet Duke.

13:24.874 --> 13:28.843
♪

13:30.156 --> 13:33.515
- You got into an actual fight with Eddie?
- You told me to!

13:33.571 --> 13:35.104
I told you to talk to him.

13:35.164 --> 13:36.329
I didn't say anything about

13:36.398 --> 13:38.031
crashing through a wall of glass.

13:38.099 --> 13:40.333
- You're a grown-up.
- He built a whole sound booth

13:40.402 --> 13:42.268
without my permission.
Whose side are you on?

13:42.337 --> 13:43.536
Yours, honey.

13:43.605 --> 13:45.405
But there is a reason you hired Eddie.

13:45.473 --> 13:48.107
He pushes you, and that's a good thing.

13:48.143 --> 13:49.709
Look, I know you're hurting.

13:49.778 --> 13:51.477
Yeah, particularly where
the glass shards

13:51.579 --> 13:53.713
- are still embedded.
- But if Eddie didn't do

13:53.782 --> 13:54.947
what Eddie always does,

13:55.016 --> 13:57.750
you would be a totally different guy.

13:57.786 --> 14:01.154
He's a pain in the ass, I know,
but he's good for you.

14:01.222 --> 14:05.124
You're so smart...
always know what to say.

14:05.193 --> 14:07.794
No! No, I really don't. [Sighs]

14:07.862 --> 14:10.563
After I assassinated
that blue morpho today,

14:10.632 --> 14:12.865
Soraya wouldn't even sit with me
on the bus-ride home.

14:12.934 --> 14:14.367
In fact, none of them would.

14:14.436 --> 14:16.569
They kept calling me
"Madame Murder-Fly".

14:16.638 --> 14:18.738
That sounds like Noah B.'s handiwork.

14:18.807 --> 14:20.440
He roasted me for like
10 minutes straight.

14:20.508 --> 14:22.742
He's like a pre-pubescent Don Rickles.

14:22.811 --> 14:24.310
Why couldn't I just turn my phone off

14:24.379 --> 14:25.445
for a couple hours?

14:25.513 --> 14:27.780
Because your job
is very important to you.

14:27.882 --> 14:30.249
And you love it. And you're a badass!

14:30.318 --> 14:32.552
Come on, you do murder trials

14:32.620 --> 14:34.420
and defend innocent people.

14:34.522 --> 14:36.122
I promise you, babe...

14:36.191 --> 14:38.191
I promise you, one day,
Soraya will realize

14:38.259 --> 14:40.393
how awesome and cool you are.

14:40.495 --> 14:41.928
Thank you.

14:41.996 --> 14:43.663
I guess I just wish there
was something I could do

14:43.731 --> 14:46.566
to make her realize it now.

14:46.634 --> 14:48.912
Hold on.

14:48.992 --> 14:50.069
Maybe there is.

14:50.138 --> 14:53.206
[Up-tempo music plays]

14:53.875 --> 14:55.341
What? I thought I'd kick it up a notch.

14:55.443 --> 14:57.977
Okay, can you go do
your homework, please?

14:58.079 --> 14:59.946
- He's really good.
- He's fine.

14:59.981 --> 15:01.781
Wait till he tries "Eye of the Tiger".

15:03.585 --> 15:06.085
Okay, people, now we have
a special visitor.

15:07.655 --> 15:08.855
[Children gasp]

15:08.957 --> 15:12.024
- It's her!
- The Butterfly Slayer!

15:12.127 --> 15:13.326
Mom, what are you doing here?

15:13.428 --> 15:15.194
Well, I just wanted to tell everyone

15:15.263 --> 15:17.430
how sorry I am
about what happened yesterday.

15:17.499 --> 15:19.265
It was actually my first field trip,

15:19.334 --> 15:22.034
and I didn't know the ropes
because I spend most of my time

15:22.137 --> 15:23.970
at a place where there
are no butterflies.

15:24.038 --> 15:25.905
How many were there when you started?

15:25.930 --> 15:26.783
[Laughter]

15:26.815 --> 15:28.982
- Noah, sit down.
- Okay.

15:29.010 --> 15:31.277
Well, I actually spend most
of my time in a courtroom

15:31.346 --> 15:32.778
because I'm a lawyer.

15:32.847 --> 15:34.573
Now, does anyone know
what a lawyer does?

15:35.884 --> 15:38.184
Okay, well, a lawyer defends people

15:38.219 --> 15:40.386
who are accused of doing bad things.

15:40.455 --> 15:41.687
Like stepping on a butterfly?

15:41.756 --> 15:43.289
Exactly, Zoe S.!

15:43.391 --> 15:46.325
- So, I talked to Ms. Hopkins...
- Conway.

15:46.427 --> 15:48.461
Conway, and she said

15:48.530 --> 15:49.962
that you can spend the rest of the day

15:50.064 --> 15:51.531
doing your multiplication tables,

15:51.633 --> 15:53.733
or I can stick around

15:53.801 --> 15:55.902
and you can put me on trial for murder.

15:56.004 --> 15:57.503
- Who's up for that?
- Me!

15:57.605 --> 15:58.671
Me!

15:58.740 --> 16:00.039
Let's do the murder!

16:00.141 --> 16:01.741
Murder! Murder!

16:01.809 --> 16:05.878
[All chanting "Murder!"]

16:05.980 --> 16:08.948
♪

16:09.017 --> 16:10.683
Eddie's still not here?

16:10.785 --> 16:12.018
I don't think he's coming in at all.

16:12.120 --> 16:13.419
Why? Did he call you?

16:13.521 --> 16:14.987
What did he say about me?
Never mind. I don't even care.

16:15.056 --> 16:16.489
Well, since you clearly don't care,

16:16.558 --> 16:18.024
there's something that
I think you should hear.

16:18.126 --> 16:19.392
Ben's demo? I know.

16:19.460 --> 16:20.526
He sent it to me, too.

16:20.628 --> 16:23.062
I'm torn bause he's really amazing,

16:23.164 --> 16:25.998
but the rate he quoted me
was just obnoxious.

16:26.100 --> 16:27.099
Not that.

16:29.704 --> 16:30.736
[Beep]

16:30.838 --> 16:32.605
EDDIE: <i>Testing, testing.
One, two, three.</i>

16:32.674 --> 16:35.241
<i>Okay, so, it's 6:00 in the morning.</i>

16:35.276 --> 16:38.277
<i>This is the inaugural recording
of our new booth.</i>

16:38.346 --> 16:40.146
<i>Me and some guys...
don't worry about it...</i>

16:40.248 --> 16:42.081
<i>we've been working all night,</i>

16:42.116 --> 16:44.450
<i>and I cannot wait
for Alex to see this thing.</i>

16:44.519 --> 16:48.254
<i>I finally did something
I know he's gonna be proud of.</i>

16:48.323 --> 16:50.556
[Beep]

16:50.625 --> 16:51.958
Then it's just, like,
seven minutes of him

16:52.060 --> 16:53.960
trying to turn off the recorder.

16:54.028 --> 16:55.394
Eventually, he just unplugs it.

16:55.496 --> 16:59.498
♪

16:59.601 --> 17:01.701
- Hey, Aunt Louise.
- Hey, Alex!

17:01.769 --> 17:03.569
What are you doing here? Come on in!

17:03.638 --> 17:04.837
- Hi.
- Oh, wow.

17:04.906 --> 17:06.271
Is... Is Eddie here?

17:06.374 --> 17:07.940
I can't find him. I tried
to get him on the phone.

17:08.009 --> 17:09.942
- He's not at his house.
- Oh, yeah, I heard.

17:09.978 --> 17:12.612
- You had one of your eruptions.
- Well, we don't have label it.

17:12.714 --> 17:14.347
All right, just a minute.

17:18.519 --> 17:19.618
Alex wants to see you.

17:19.686 --> 17:20.819
Tell him I'm not here.

17:20.855 --> 17:22.255
He knows you're here!

17:22.323 --> 17:23.656
Your car's in the driveway.

17:23.724 --> 17:25.324
Well, did he see it? Take my keys,

17:25.393 --> 17:27.593
- move it around back.
- I'm not supposed to drive!

17:27.694 --> 17:28.861
It's like 40 feet.

17:28.930 --> 17:30.329
Go talk to him!

17:30.398 --> 17:32.431
I swear to God, Ma.

17:32.533 --> 17:34.867
Oh, no one told me you were here.

17:34.969 --> 17:36.369
Why didn't you come to work, Ed?

17:36.471 --> 17:37.570
Well, when the boss tells you

17:37.672 --> 17:38.938
he wishes he never hired you...

17:38.973 --> 17:40.339
I'm sorry I said that, okay?

17:40.441 --> 17:42.041
And I'm sorry I broke your booth.

17:42.110 --> 17:43.809
Well, I'm sorry I made it
without asking,

17:43.878 --> 17:45.945
but I was really just trying to help.

17:46.047 --> 17:47.346
It just felt like you were treating me

17:47.448 --> 17:48.547
like when we were kids.

17:48.583 --> 17:50.816
You were always pushing me
around and bullying me.

17:50.885 --> 17:52.151
I did no such thing.

17:52.220 --> 17:54.020
You once replaced my lip gloss
with crazy glue

17:54.122 --> 17:56.088
when I was supposed to sing
the "Star-Spangled Banner".

17:56.124 --> 17:58.658
- I had to hum it.
- You still hit that high note.

17:58.726 --> 17:59.892
Yeah, I did.

17:59.961 --> 18:02.795
Truth is, I was always
a little jealous of you, Al,

18:02.864 --> 18:04.697
so I did some dumb stuff.

18:04.766 --> 18:06.165
- Jealous?
- Of course.

18:06.234 --> 18:08.334
You were the smart one...
the one with the big ideas.

18:08.403 --> 18:10.403
You were going places.
I always knew that.

18:10.505 --> 18:12.672
And look at you now. I was right.

18:12.740 --> 18:14.073
So when you asked me
to come work for you,

18:14.175 --> 18:15.675
I couldn't even believe it.

18:15.710 --> 18:17.877
- Really?
- I guess I've been trying to prove

18:17.945 --> 18:20.279
you made a good choice ever since.

18:20.381 --> 18:22.715
Maybe I try a little too hard sometimes.

18:22.784 --> 18:25.051
Bus-bench ads might have
been a bridge too far.

18:25.119 --> 18:26.619
It wasn't a great photo. I see that now.

18:26.688 --> 18:28.387
Why was I wearing a construction hat?

18:28.489 --> 18:30.222
Anyway, from now on,

18:30.325 --> 18:32.591
I'll stop making you do things
you don't want to do.

18:32.660 --> 18:34.260
Well, don't stop completely.

18:34.295 --> 18:37.096
'Cause the truth is,
sometimes I need a little push.

18:37.198 --> 18:39.098
Give me a hug, come on.

18:39.200 --> 18:42.134
All right.

18:42.236 --> 18:44.370
LOUISE: Are you hugging?
That sounds like a hug!

18:44.472 --> 18:46.505
- Ma, give us some space!
- All right!

18:46.574 --> 18:47.707
We're hugging.

18:47.809 --> 18:49.241
We're hugging.

18:49.344 --> 18:51.177
ALEX: <i>It turned out Rooni was right.</i>

18:51.245 --> 18:54.413
<i>I needed Eddie for lots of reasons.</i>

18:54.482 --> 18:56.582
<i>For starters, he helped me
put the booth back together.</i>

18:56.684 --> 18:59.185
♪

18:59.287 --> 19:00.886
<i>And he even figured out
a way to get Marion</i>

19:00.955 --> 19:02.288
<i>to waive his rent increase.</i>

19:02.390 --> 19:06.892
[Vocalizing]

19:06.961 --> 19:09.061
I have known this woman for eight years.

19:09.163 --> 19:11.797
You guys have probably only
known her for one day.

19:11.866 --> 19:14.300
<i>I guess not matter how well
you know someone,</i>

19:14.369 --> 19:16.068
<i>there's still a lot to learn about them.</i>

19:16.170 --> 19:18.904
♪

19:18.973 --> 19:20.306
<i>And with a little effort,</i>

19:20.375 --> 19:22.541
<i>it's possible to see them
in a brand-new light.</i>

19:22.643 --> 19:25.845
[Laughter]

19:25.947 --> 19:27.279
<i>And in the end, the people you love</i>

19:27.382 --> 19:28.981
<i>may make your life difficult,</i>

19:29.016 --> 19:32.184
they may "accidently" give you rabies,

19:32.286 --> 19:35.187
but they will always have your back.

19:35.289 --> 19:39.291
♪

19:39.394 --> 19:41.193
Damn, buddy. That is so amazing.

19:41.295 --> 19:42.862
Are you sure you won't
budge on your fee?

19:42.964 --> 19:44.697
Sorry, Dad. My hands are tied.

19:44.799 --> 19:47.400
Well, I gave it a try.

19:47.468 --> 19:48.601
Thanks anyway.

19:48.703 --> 19:50.436
Fine! I'll do it!

19:50.538 --> 19:52.805
Man, you drive a hard bargain.

19:52.907 --> 19:54.440
Where'd you learn
to negotiate like that?

19:54.542 --> 19:58.144
A little site called YouTube.

19:58.212 --> 19:59.311
Damn it!

20:00.413 --> 20:04.155
And so, you must find
that my mom is innocent

20:04.218 --> 20:07.920
because she killed
the butterfly by accident.

20:09.057 --> 20:11.257
[Whispering] You did so good.

20:11.359 --> 20:12.691
Oh, now ask if they've
reached a verdict.

20:12.794 --> 20:14.827
Everybody who thinks she's guilty,

20:14.929 --> 20:16.495
raise your hand.

20:16.531 --> 20:18.998
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight, nine...

20:19.100 --> 20:21.500
I can't even count that high. Guilty!

20:21.602 --> 20:22.992
Don't worry. They're biased.

20:23.039 --> 20:24.890
We just had a unit on butterflies.

20:24.958 --> 20:27.984
Next on the docket...
Smelt It v. Dealt It.

20:28.078 --> 20:30.028
Let's do this.
